                                    <p style="">Our Asheville, NC office operates under the business entity Amec Foster Wheeler Environment &amp; Infrastructure, Inc. Since the establishment of our local office in 1987, we have proudly served clients in Western North Carolina with excellence in facilities-related consulting, water resources, environmental sciences and remediation, geotechnical engineering, and materials testing services. Today we have 13 local professional and technical support personnel sitting in-house to support Asheville and the Western Carolina region. &nbsp;</p><div style="">The office provides multi-discipline engineering, project management, and construction management services for public and private sector clients, including municipalities, industrial/commercial firms and educational establishments, to name a few.&nbsp;</div><div><br /></div><div>Our team provides a strong knowledge of the local market conditions, and maintains a thorough understanding of both municipal and states codes and regulations. Through our more than 60 years of experience in North Carolina we have become familiar with working alongside and in accordance with protocols and procedures set by the State Construction Office.&nbsp;</div><div><br /></div><div>Specific services provided:</div><div><ul><li>Civil;</li><li>Environmental;</li><li>Hydrogeology;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Remediation;</li><li>Geotechnical;</li><li>Construction Materials Testing;</li><li>Water Resources;</li><li>Non-Destructive Testing;</li><li>Program / Construction Management;</li><li>Environmental Health &amp; Safety.</li></ul></div><div style="">Amec Foster Wheeler has an integrated resource pool across the Carolinas including offices in Asheville, Wilmington, Charlotte and Durham, North Carolina as well as Columbia and Greenville, South Carolina. The resources from these locations work together on many projects, depending on the size, scale and scheduling requirements.</div>
                                







