                                    <div>Our Durham office operates under the business entity Amec Foster Wheeler Environment &amp; Infrastructure, Inc. The office is comprised of more than 160 professional and technical support personnel, providing a substantial resource pool for undertaking major projects locally, and across the south east region.</div><div><br /></div><div>The office provides multi-discipline engineering, air compliance, remediation, water resources, project management, and construction management services for public and private sector clients. Major clients served from this office include:</div><div><br /></div><div><ul><li>State of North Carolina;</li><li>Bechtel Power Corporation;</li><li>Duke Energy;</li><li>US Environmental Protection Agency;</li><li>North Carolina Department of Transportation;</li><li>Parsons Brinckerhoff;</li><li>Duke University;</li><li>US Department of Agriculture;</li><li>Norfolk Southern Corporation;</li><li>CSX Transportation, Inc.&nbsp;</li></ul></div><div style="">Amec Foster Wheeler has executed projects for a variety of customers, providing a strong knowledge of the local market conditions and players in terms of project services, consultancy, construction companies and suppliers. Personnel in Durham have a thorough understanding of both municipal and regional codes and regulations, and are registered in several states to carry out engineering and geology.</div><div style="">Specific services provided:&nbsp;</div><div><br /></div><div><ul><li>Air Compliance;</li><li>Civil Engineering;</li><li>Environmental Engineering;</li><li>Geotechnical Engineering;</li><li>Hydrogeology;</li><li>Remediation;</li><li>Water Resources;</li><li>Construction Materials Testing;</li><li>Non-Destructive Testing;</li><li>Project Management;</li><li>Program and Construction Management;</li><li>Environment, Health and Safety (EHS);</li><li>Nuclear.</li></ul></div><div>Amec Foster Wheeler has an integrated resource pool across the Carolinas including offices located in Durham, Wilmington, Asheville, and Charlotte, North Carolina as well as Columbia and Greenville, South Carolina. Additionally, our Richmond, Virginia branch falls under the leadership of the Durham office. The resources from these locations work together on many projects, depending on the size, scale and scheduling requirements.<br /></div><p style=""><br /><br /></p>
                                







