                                    <div>This location operates as Amec Foster Wheeler Environment &amp; Infrastructure, Inc. Established in 1950, the Charlotte, NC office is staffed with more than 100 full-time professional engineers, scientists, geologists, field/laboratory technicians and support staff. Our professionals provide a full range of disciplines, from subsurface exploration to property condition assessment to environmental remediation. In addition, this location maintains in-house full-service geotechnical and materials testing laboratories.</div><div><br /></div><div>The office provides multi-discipline engineering, environmental, project management, and construction management services for public and private sector clients. Amec Foster Wheeler has proudly served clients in North Carolina with excellence in geotechnical engineering, materials testing, structural engineering, water resources, environmental sciences and remediation, and hydrogeology. The local Charlotte team provide professional services for a variety of project types, including infrastructure, transportation, energy, landfills, commercial development and educational facilities. &nbsp;</div><div><br /></div><div>Major clients served from this office include:</div><div><ul><li>Duke Energy;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>City of Charlotte;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>North Carolina Department of Transportation;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>University of North Carolina at Charlotte;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Charlotte Douglas International Airport;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>CSX Transportation, Inc;&nbsp;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>BB&amp;T;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>CBRE;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>US Department of Veterans Association.&nbsp;</li></ul></div><div style="">Specific services provided:&nbsp;</div><div style=""><ul><li>Civil;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Environmental;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Hydrogeology;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Remediation;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Geotechnical;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Water Resources;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Construction Materials Testing;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Structural Engineering / Forensics;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Non-destructive testing;&nbsp;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Program / Construction Management;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Environmental Health &amp; Safety;<br /></li></ul></div><div style="">Amec Foster Wheeler has an integrated resource pool across the Carolinas including offices located Charlotte, Wilmington, Asheville and Durham, North Carolina as well as Columbia and Greenville, South Carolina. The resources from these locations work together on many projects, depending on the size, scale and scheduling requirements.</div><div style=""><br /></div><div style="">Amec Foster Wheeler AES, Inc., a specialist nuclear services provider, also operates from this office.<br /></div>
                                







