                                    <h2>Hamilton</h2><p><br/><p>The Hamilton and St. Catharines offices operate work closely as one team of 90 engineers, geoscientists, technologists and cultural heritage professionals. </p><p>We specialize in materials engineering, geotechnical engineering, environmental assessments, environmental compliance auditing, water resources work, archaeology and built heritage. As well as environmental services including management systems, sustainability and brownfield redevelopment.<br />&nbsp;<br />We are a leading provider of geotechnical, environmental, water resources, cultural heritage resources and materials engineering services, including support for forensic investigations and litigation.<br />&nbsp;<br />At one time a highly industrialized area, many of the industries in the Hamilton-Niagara area have disappeared and their sites need to be cleaned up.&nbsp; As a result, AMEC is doing a lot of brownfields work, which includes site assessment, risk assessment and site remediation and site redevelopment.<br /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
                                







