                                    <h2>St. John's, Newfoundland&nbsp;</h2><p style="">Our St. John's office includes over 150 professional and technical support personnel that provide a substantial resource pool for undertaking major projects locally, across Canada and abroad. We provide multi-discipline engineering, architecture, procurement, project management, and construction management services for public and private sector clients.</p><p>Amec Foster Wheeler has an integrated resource pool across a number of offices in Atlantic Canada including St John’s, Dartmouth, Fredericton, Sydney and Moncton.&nbsp; The resources from these locations work together on many projects depending on the size, scale and scheduling requirements.</p><p>We have executed projects for many customers in several sectors providing a strong knowledge of the local market conditions and players in terms of project services, consultancy, construction companies and suppliers.&nbsp;Amec Foster Wheeler in Newfoundland and Labrador has a thorough understanding of both municipal and provincial codes and regulations and is registered in most Canadian provinces to carry out engineering and architecture.</p><p>We also provide materials development and testing through our Materials Engineering Laboratory located on Pippy Place, St. John’s. This facility offers a full suite of materials testing, including soil, concrete and asphalt. </p><p>The main lines of business include:</p><p><strong>Infrastructure:</strong> Water &amp; sewer systems, roads, bridges, and marine structures. <br /><strong>Environmental:</strong> Contaminated sites and waste management <br /><strong>Buildings:</strong>&nbsp;Design and project management of hospitals, universities, office complexes, and commercial facilities. <br /><strong>Industrial:</strong>&nbsp;Refineries and plants, forestry, and mining. <br /><strong>Energy: </strong>Oil &amp; gas, hydropower, and thermal power plants<br /></p><p>Specific services provided: <br />Professional Services <br />- Architecture <br />- Civil engineering <br />- Environmental engineering<br />- Geotechnical engineering<br />- Structural engineering <br />- Mechanical engineering <br />- Electrical engineering <br />- Marine engineering <br />- Instrumentation and controls <br />- Project management<br />- Materials and engineering laboratory services<br /></p><p>Amec Foster Wheeler has provided services throughout NL and Atlantic Canada through its predecessor companies, AGRA Shawmont and BFL for over 50 years. Major clients include: <br />- Department of National Defence <br />- Public Works &amp; Government Services Canada <br />- Health Care Corporation of St John’s <br />- North Atlantic Refinery Limited <br />- Iron Ore Company of Canada <br />- Memorial University <br />- ExxonMobil <br />- Department of Transportation &amp; Public Works NL<br />- Brookfield Lepage <br />- Nalcor<br />- Nova Scotia Power<br />- Newfoundland Power <br />- Bowater Mersey <br />- Regional municipalities <br />- Various private project developers</p>
                                







