                                    <div>Our Wilmington, NC office operates under the business entity Amec Foster Wheeler Environment &amp; Infrastructure, Inc. This office has been supporting the local coastal community and national clients for more than 25 years, and is comprised of an experienced team of more than 20 engineers, hydrogeologists, environmental scientists and engineering technicians.&nbsp;</div><div><br /></div><div>The main practice areas for much of the past 25 years has been in environmental, construction and water-related services. The major clients and projects in the Wilmington office tend to be industrial in nature. Major clients served from this office include:&nbsp;</div><div><br /></div><div><ul><li>General Electric;</li><li>Honeywell International;</li><li>Potash Corporation;</li><li>North Carolina State Ports;</li><li>US Department of the Navy;</li><li>Phillips Lighting Company;</li><li>Duke Energy.</li></ul></div><div style="">Amec Foster Wheeler personnel in Wilmington have a thorough understanding of both municipal and regional codes and regulations, and are registered in several states to carry out engineering and geology.</div><div><br /></div><div>Our primary services are hydrogeology, environmental engineering and sciences, environmental investigation and remediation, permitting and planning. The office also holds experience in water resources, coastal resources, construction inspection and civil engineering, and performs a full suite of materials testing, including soil, concrete and asphalt. Specific services provided:</div><div><ul><li>Civil;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Environmental;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Hydrogeology;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Remediation;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Construction materials testing;</li><li><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"></span>Water resources.</li></ul></div><div style="">Amec Foster Wheeler has an integrated resource pool across the Carolinas including offices located in Wilmington, Asheville, Charlotte and Durham, North Carolina as well as Columbia and Greenville, South Carolina. The resources from these locations work together on many projects, depending on the size, scale and scheduling requirements.</div>
                                







